    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This cloth of gold cape was originally gifted to one of Goka's emperors centuries ago. Since then, it has spawned many imitations, which are all alike in that they are dyed with an elaborate seal depicting two drakes flanking Goka's palace and the Seven Dragons Bridge. The beautiful cape grants you a +3 item bonus to checks to Lie and to Make an Impression. While you wear the cape, the weather (including wind and fog) doesn't affect your movement or vision. Additionally, whenever you fall while wearing the *cape of the open sky*, the cape automatically casts *feather fall* on you.",
        "level": 18,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Invested",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 98,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 219,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
                "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "invest",
                        "alt": "invest",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2799
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Transmutation",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                            "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        },
                        "page": 637,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "4.0",
                            "alt": "4.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e15261ef9d67eae23579ccf106d27c86",
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the transmutation school of magic, typically changing something\u2019s form.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
